  "body": "Right now, whenever a member node receives a magnet link, it'll process it if the following conditions are met:\r\n\r\n1. The magnetlink originates from a community that the member node is part of (the currently logged in user is a member)\r\n2. The magnetlink was signed by the community (owner)\r\n3. The magnetlink's clock is >= the last processed magnetlink's clock\r\n\r\nMagnetlinks are emitted whenever the owner node seeds the torrent. This happens when:\r\n\r\n1. New archives are created (every 7 days, assuming the owner node is online)\r\n2. Whenever the owner node starts the node\r\n\r\nIn case of 2) no new archives were created so the resulting magnetlink is going to be the same as the one that was dispatched the last time.\r\n\r\nEven though the magnetlink is the same as the previous one, it still meets all 3 criteria mentioned above for a member node to process it (it will then realize that there's no new archives to download and cancel, but still it'll try to fetch the torrent info etc).\r\n\r\nFor such cases, it'd make sense to keep track of the last successfully handled magnetlink, so that we can use it to compare it with any incoming magnetlinks. If the incoming one is indeed the exact same, we can ignore it.",
